Introduction

Shohei is a Japanese singer and rapper under SM Entertainment. He is a member of the trot-idol group MYTRO.

On July 2, 2022, he was introduced as a member of the trainee team SM Rookies, along with Eunseok and Seunghan.

Although initially slated to join NCT New Team, he was unable to do so due to a severe back injury in May 2023. However, SM Entertainment clarified that he remains with the company and has plans for future solo activities.

Before joining SM, he was a member of the Japanese boy group BXB.
